    div.visual.row
      div.content
        h2 Made for the hackers
        p Install it with bower and you will be able to integrate Picnic in any project and make it work for you.
        p Picnic is written in SCSS with <a href="#">many variables</a> and <a href="#"><em>classes</em> (placeholders)</a> to make it easy to extend.
        a.button.icon-file-code Documentation
        | 
        a.button.icon-g Github
      pre.
        // Define your own main color
        $picnic-primary: #faa;

        // Add picnic to your codebase
        @include 'bower/picnic/src/picnic';

        // Create a new element
        .call-to-action {
          @extends %button;
        }

